[next]
step = "MERGE-ORCHESTRATION SYSTEM COMPLETE + AUTONOMY LOOP CLOSED + SCHEDULED (cron + tick). Full pipeline on main: SENSE Sensor (#492) + producer observe.sh (#78); DELIBERATE Strategist + KinCompetence/Kin.Council (#494); RUNTIME TIER KinGate + FileStore (#494); LIVE LOOP (#495); SCHEDULED TRIGGER Scheduler.cycle + mix hypatia.merge_orchestrate (#496); ACTUATE Dispatcher manifest -> .git-private-farm actuate.sh (#77). CRON+TICK (this commit): (1) TICK -- Hypatia.MergeOrchestration.Ticker GenServer (mirrors LearningScheduler: send_after :tick -> guarded do_cycle -> reschedule; run_now/status; a cycle failure is rescued+recorded, never crashes the tick). Wired into application.ex via merge_orchestration_children() mirroring tui_children() -- DEFAULT OFF, enabled by `config :hypatia, :merge_orchestration, enabled: true, interval_ms: 900_000`. (2) CRON -- .github/workflows/merge-orchestrate.yml: schedule (hourly 17 * * * *) + workflow_dispatch, SHA-pinned setup-beam/checkout/cache/upload, runs `mix hypatia.merge_orchestrate --store $MERGE_ORCH_STORE` (store from vars.MERGE_ORCH_STORE||data/verisim), uploads merge-decisions.jsonl artifact (if-no-files-found: ignore). Token-free: both compute+write the manifest; the farm actuator (separate, PAT) merges. Tests: 64 ExUnit (was 61: +3 Ticker -- do_cycle happy/records-stats, do_cycle guarded-failure [encoder raises -> rescued, runs stays 0], GenServer run_now->status), 0 failures, local elixir 1.14, mix-format-clean, scanner-clean. PR pending: hypatia (Ticker + app wiring + cron workflow). THE SYSTEM IS NOW FULLY SCHEDULABLE end-to-end. REMAINING = pure owner config/ops, NO code: flip `config :hypatia, :merge_orchestration, enabled: true` to run the in-brain tick, and/or set repo var MERGE_ORCH_STORE + let the cron run (point at a populated store + add push-to-actuator if desired); a5 standards adoption (owner-applied); P3 handshake + mass_squash in actuator; .git-private-farm Actions billing is dead -- fix before the actuator runs scheduled."

[post-completion-followons]
# Owner picked all four 2026-06-14 (P3/mass_squash, BoA design doc, a5 draft, add-BoA-to-scope).
p3-mass-squash = "LANDED .git-private-farm PR #79: decide_action gains P3 (FARM_P3_AUTHORIZED=1 owner handshake) + mass_squash (campaign_ref + $FARM_CAMPAIGN_DIR/<ref>.active marker) gates, both owner-held signals the brain can't self-grant. 10/10 bash conformance (was 5), shellcheck-clean, resolves TODO(increment-3b). Farm CI dead-infra (404), admin-merge like #78."
boa-substrate = "DESIGN DOC landed (#498) + BatonEmitter BUILT (this commit). bag-of-actions still NOT in MCP scope (owner granted GitHub permission but the session's 11-repo MCP scope is fixed; add_repo tool unavailable) -- so read its REAL API by public git clone to /tmp/boa. Findings: Bag.Mesh.submit_planned(spec, budget) where spec=%{check_id,command,required_cap,mutating?,risk?}; planner routes to cheapest capable node + GATES mutating:true work on a verifier (= the independent re-verify); a merge is just command=[gh,pr,merge,...] with required_cap=\"secret-access\" -- the capability ONLY mesh-github-runner holds in nodes.scm (the token-bearer; brain's node lacks it -> Baton migrates = token-free-brain as capability routing). NO bag-of-actions changes needed for the command-based merge. Hypatia.MergeOrchestration.BatonEmitter: to_spec/2 (pure -> the submit_planned spec, carrying lease+route+rationale as residue/attestation) + emit/2 (one Baton per ARMED Loop entry; Bag.Mesh call late-bound via apply/3 + injectable, so compile-decoupled + tests dep-free). 74 ExUnit (was 71: +3 BatonEmitter). REMAINING on BoA: when bag-of-actions is in a session's MCP scope, wire emit into the live loop as the alt actuation backend (alongside write_manifest) + register hypatia as a mesh node; no new emitter logic."
a5-standards = "DRAFT-ONLY pending owner approval (standards is ask-before-touching/license-sensitive): fill INTENT.contractile with the a5 lease/claim schema as an intent-kind + extend TRUST.contractile with the meta trust-deny (an agent cannot self-authorise a meta claim). To be drafted + shown, NOT pushed, until owner signs off the exact text."
manifest-shape-seam = "RESOLVED .git-private-farm PR #80 (merged): actuate.sh gains normalize_manifest (jq adapter mapping BOTH the flat artifact-1 shape AND the brain's nested tier/strategy+.merge merge-decisions.jsonl entry to the flat fields decide_action needs; flat wins so existing manifests unchanged) + actuate_jsonl (consume a whole merge-decisions.jsonl, one decision/line). 13/13 bash conformance (was 10), shellcheck-clean. The sense->deliberate->gate->manifest->actuate loop is now connected end to end."
k9-lease-validator = "LANDED hypatia (this commit): Hypatia.MergeOrchestration.LeaseValidator + mix hypatia.validate_leases -- the a5 k9 lease validator. Audits the PERSISTED lease store (what KinGate.decide_acquire can't see across files): LE1 (held=>TTL), LE2 (held meta=>owner_authorized), stale (held past TTL), overlap (>=2 live held leases on one repo -- the per-repo rule broken in the store). validate/2 pure; validate_store/2 over FileStore.list; Mix task exits non-zero on any violation (CI gate). 71 ExUnit (was 64: +7 LeaseValidator). The standards-side k9 contractile registration is part of the a5 draft (owner-approval-pending; the drafted INTENT probe points at this validator)."
